The article discusses how innovations in artificial intelligence (AI) are benefiting various areas such as personalized cancer treatments, search and rescue disaster response, and safer roadways with automated vehicles. However, concerns about data privacy, big tech companies, and technology-enabled authoritarianism have raised questions about the moral implications of embracing AI. The article argues that it is possible to advance emerging technology while still adhering to values such as freedom, human rights, and respect for human dignity. As part of the American AI Initiative, the White House is proposing a set of regulatory principles to govern AI development in the private sector, aiming to address the technical and ethical challenges posed by AI.